caption: Visited today for both dine in and take out meals. Early afternoon dine-in tapas were fantastic, evening takeout tapas were just as good if not even better! Attention to detail by the staff and wine recommendations were top-notch! I'll be frequenting them every time I'm back in DC.

Last week was our first time in this fine restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last time. We had a good time with the good service, with the exceptional  meal and booze and with the modest charge. We will absolutely come back again.
They offer a vast range of delicious food. I liked eating here. The employees are always super nice, pricing is affordable and the spot is always neat.
I got the Dragon Blend tea and it was great! Light and sweet. The space is adorable and i love the music they're playing. Decor is cute as well. Very relaxing tea house vibes. Service was awesome.
The older man at the register was handling my food with his bare hands. He scooped the ginger and wasabi from their containers with his fingers and slathered it across my plate. Unhygienic. Hard pass
So good! Little mom and pop shop!

Experienced the sushi bar(omakase-chef's choice) and it was a great choice. Seating at the counter, you had a great view of Seoul through the windows at the back of the bar. Chef, was great, explaining the dishes, telling little jokes (would only speak English if it was raining (it wasn't), and made GREAT sushi. Ingredients are critical, he used fresh seafood, Don't really speak Korea, but chef was fluent in Japanese and did speak a little English. Regardless, made us feel comfortable and welcome to his space. Best sushi served in Seoul, comparable to what you would see in Japan. Chef made us feel so welcome, his invitation to return to see him again, felt real sincere. Never was asked to return to a restaurant before.
Delicious udon, friendly family atmosphere...excellent!!!

The best Japanese restaurant I've been in DC area. Really sweet couple runs the place. The food was amazing,  impeccable! Great flavor,  texture,  presentation, everything 10/10. I ordered a bento, sunomono and gyoza and all was almost perfect. The only downside is that I found it a little pricey.
Small place, 7 tables? but great food and a nice place to enjoy something to eat. Lovely old couple, I assume, running the place.
This place was so enchanting. Don't expect posh decor or frills, just real, authentic,  great food. So good!

Pretty basic sushi. But we kinda expected it. I didn't expect the specially rolls to be so expensive, so we just ended up getting a couple "regular" rolls. Nothing to write home about, but service was fast and we were craving sushi, so we were happy
Super cozy moms and pops spot!the food is amazing!

(Translated by Google) With a group of 8, we had a great meal. The service was fast and the meal was excellent. I took ramen and they reminded me of my trip to Japan. My Japanese colleague confirmed to me that they were very good. The salmon sushi was perfect. The atmosphere is very friendly and we were very well received.  (Original) Avec un groupe de 8, on a passé un excellent repas. Le service était rapide et le repas était excellent. J'ai pris des ramens et ils m'ont rappelés mon voyage au Japon. Ma collègue japonaise m'a confirmé qu'ils étaient très bons. Les sushis au saumon étaient parfaits. L'ambiance est très amicale et nous avons étés très bien reçus.

I don't often get to go out and eat ramen because most of the ramen places around us make their broths with mushrooms and, while I used to love eating mushrooms, my body hates mushrooms so this was a nice surprise!  The dining room was a bit small/cramped but this food was totally worth it. Plus the service was quick so it made for a quick turnover in the dining area.  The red ginger that came in my ramen was such a perfect flavor that I kept savoring it everytime I got a bit. There was a great balance of noodles to broth to the rest of the ingredients for both the ramen and the udon and that boiled egg was absolutely a treat in my ramen.  I would happily go back here!
Mom and pop restaurant. Great sushi at a good price for downtown D.C.  We will be back.
Classic little Japanese joint. Great lunch boxes.
My daughter and i tried this place!  Its amazing!  However, the hours arent exactly as posted here.  Ive tried to return several times only to find the place closed 🤔

(Translated by Google) I'm a Korean couple, but I'm very unkind. 4 people I had 2 ramen sushi boxes 2 more spoons make me notice  Ramen noodles are so big Even the noodles are not ripe and stick together Real money too much  (Original) 한국인 부부라고해서 왔는데 대박 불친절함. 4명이서 라면 2개 스시박스2개 시켰는데 숟가락 2개 더달라하니 완전 눈치줌  라면은 물한컵 다넣어도 모자를만큼 엄청 짬 심지어 면이 익지도않아서 뭉쳐있음 진짜 돈 너무아까운 곳
Best sashimi ever! Thick pieces of fish in the sushi! I was so full. Very good quality
(Translated by Google) It's good, fresh and correct. Service speed and smiling.  (Original) C'est bon, frais et correcte. Service speed et souriant.
A great find in DC! Small hole in the wall with inside and outside seating available. Service is good and the food is so good!
I tried 1 californa roll, my friends tried combo roll and the we feel the taste is so so . The restaurant looks cozy and is run by 1 old couple. It is near Capitol Hill

Friday the Momo box was perfect! Sadly on Saturday we had to order “normal” sushi. The quality is great, the service is really friendly and the food was really really good! Such a place to recommend from a service and pricing perspective.

Very cool spot in DC for sushi. Very nice server who was able to accommodate for my larger party of guys after a job had been done. The sushi selection was good and tasted great. Very cool experience.
NO bento box available. Maybe they took it off the menu??? Service was lovely and so was the food

Momoyama Sushi has a wide selection of creative sushi rolls and Japanese main dishes. It also has wine, beer, saki, and nonalcoholic drinks. Suggest a drop-by for lunch if you work in the area or for dinner after a happy hour visit to the two nearby bars.
Such a kind lady working as waitress.  Very nice and quick.  Great food great location.  Literally a hidden gem for Sushi and others in Washington
Small quaint place owned my a lovely couple. I have had fancier sushi many times. It was somewhat underwhelming but nevertheless, it was fresh.
Amazing food come here every year

Humble hole in the wall, family restaurant with excellent sushi, lovingly prepared.  The Japanese immigrant owners put their hearts into their food.  Exquisitely fresh ingredients,  well-made sushi nigiri and rolls.   Patio dining available in season.  Inside seating area could use an upgrade, but - to paraphrase James Carville -  “It’s the food, diners”
Excellent service, delicious, and perfectly priced.
Small place but good sushi.  Not much on atmosphere, but nice regardless.
We didn't get much food for how much we paid, but the sushi was good and the staff was very nice.

Didn't ask if it was to go or not. Randomly assumed and charged extra. Couldn't argue about it when you point it out.  Also super overpriced.  It's 15 bucks for a veggie box that they then tried to skimp on. (instead of tofu teriyaki, they put in a sad piece of tuna for it).  When you call them out, they don't say anything. I had to ask them 5 times to get it fixed.  Food isn't worth. If it wasn't closer to the capitol than other places,I would never have gotten it
Ok
Really cute place! Not a lot of people and we were served quickly. The tea tasted good, and the prices were very good for the amount of food we got, in my opinion! Will definitely be going back.

The staff here were super friendly. The food was served quickly and the sushi was tasty. The place was empty when we went which was nice, no wait time. The sushi was well priced. Not a huge selection of drinks but we just grabbed beers. The seating is very casual, just basic looking tables and chairs.
Very nice hole in the wall restaurant.  The food was amazing and the staff were very pleasant.
Friendly staffs, small space and we got food served very fast. Tasty Japanese food

The staff is nice and friendly, but the food was a problem. $16 for a set meal for sashimi is a nice deal until you see how small they cut the fish, it was thinly sliced and it tasted like it was thawed an hour ago.
All the employees were very friendly. My son spilled soy sauce, but they were kind enough to clean it up. sushi and sashimi were very fresh and delicious.
Love this place.  The best sushi and sashimi hidden right in DC.
Very good food! Really scratched my sushi itch.
We ordered randomly a few dishes from their lunch menu and everything is yummy.

The sushi was fresh and delicious, but the star of the show was the spicy miso ramen. A little pricy, but definitely worth every penny. All of our food was out within minutes, and the staff could not have been nicer!
A wholesome experience with a warm welcome from a friendly host. The sushi came quickly and fresh. My personal best experience with sushi of all time.
Excellent eel and spider rolls!!
Kind owner and great korean foods!
Good place, fresh good, good service and good price. What else?
Both Google and yelp said it's open, but when I arrived at 6:50pm on a Saturday, it was dark... And of course, closed.

(Translated by Google) I was comfortable in the position that the Korean couple is not good at English. The food is delicious and kind.  (Original) 한국인 부부께서 하시는 곳이라 영어를 잘 못하는 입장에서 편하고 좋았습니다. 음식도 맛있고 친절하십니다.
good Korean and Japanese style food, hits the apot
Delicious food! Friendly service!

In town for a conference and wanted a quiet place to eat since I'd be socializing nonstop for the past 48 hours.  This place was a block away from my hotel and was really good.  Very tiny hole in the wall place run by an elderly couple, the service was great and so was the food.   I got an Eel Box along with a spicy tuna crunch roll and some hot sake.   Really hit the spot on a cold December night.  Would definitely come back next time I'm in DC.

This small mum and pop sushi shop is amazing for a quick bite or a nice dinner.  The wife and I stopped in with our 7mo old son to get a quick dinner and this place did not disappoint! Tastey fresh and fair price, everything came out quick.  Great place to support the locals and super easy to meet up with friends!
(Translated by Google) Sushi  (Original) 스시

Came in as a large group. Took 35 minutes to get food. Beer/wine/tea came out 10 minutes after we had finished our food. Waters never came out. They tried to charge us for beverages we never received and accused us of trying to avoid paying for food. Paying for the food alone took 30 minutes.  ***UPDATE: Save your receipts and check your credit card statements! Everyone in our party was charged $2 extra! 😡
Wife was in the mood for sushi. Stopped by Saturday at 7p. All locked up. Ended up at 'The Alibi' like many others I see in the reviews.
We loved this small family owned restaurant. Delicious sushi! Wonderful place, with wonderful people, nothing fancy but comfortable and friendly.
OK food, horrible decor and atmosphere, way way way overpriced for the quality.  Friendly service but that's about it.
Said they were open but wasn't. Apparently they clean today? Anyway, it was raining and had to uber for nothing. Not cool
Excellent little resturant near the Hyatt Regency on Capital Hill. A small business, but the food and the service is great. Prices are reasonable.
(Translated by Google) Simple food. The place looks dirty  (Original) Comida simples.  O lugar parece sujo
Delicious!!! Owners are an elderly Asian couple who are delightful! Do not be fooled by the outward appearance
Amazing service, food ready in 5 minutes and greated as soon as you walk in. The food was fresh and delicious.

Mom and pop shop hidden away on C Street. The owners are an elderly Asian couple. They are very sweet and the rolls are pretty good. They have a decent variety of sushi and nigiri.  It's not an upscale sushi place but it is a pleasant loungy experience. Stay for a while, enjoy a sake with your fresh fish after a day of work. Don't be intimidated by it's atypical location.

I'd always thought the place was out of business, because most times I'd walked by, it was closed. Based upon the overall 4 star reviews and the google map note which said they have a happy hour, I went at 5:30 pm.  I was the only customer there.  The restaurant is furnished with cheap Chinese takeout restaurant style furniture and the smell was stale fish.  My daughter joined me 5 minutes later and they brought her a menu, then completely ignored us.  No water, no check-in for 20 minutes.  We left.  FYI, there is no happy hour.  The prices were the highest I've experienced at any sushi restaurant.   $55 for sushimi and teryaki combo for one, really!?  All nigeri was $7 for two pieces and rolls were $15.  Not for me.

Went for an early dinner, but we were the only ones in the restaurant; seems more like a lunch establishment due to reading other reviews where they closed early. Seems family owned, and the sushi was fresh and delicious. A little slow on service, but extremely nice and welcoming. Would return again for sushi close to the mall.
Good stuff!
Perfect food with good service!
Over priced, you are paying for location.
(Translated by Google) Very good Japanese in DC. Very well priced.  (Original) Muy buen japones en DC. Muy bien de precio.
Small place, decent good, fast and friendly service. The bento box was great to share for two people. Edamame was great!
Great sushi! Super friendly staff. It is a little hidden but it's worth finding.

Outrageously good sushi for a very good price.  I’ve been to restraints charging twice the price that are not as good as this place.  I would highly recommend coming to this place.  The only bad reviews are people complaining about it being closed.   call before you head out and check, it’s with the extra work.
Best sushi in Washington DC. Great service
Not open when they said they’d be open. I ended up at the Alibi instead which was delicious.
WAS NOT OPEN WHEN IT SAID IT WOULD BE. SO IM STANDING OUTSIDE IN THE FREEZING COLD WAITING FOR A RIDE. Wasted 12 dollars on a Lyft here.
(Translated by Google) Nice staffs. Greate shushi.  (Original) Nice staffs. Greate shushi.

As others shared, I found the restaurant closed when I arrived on Friday shortly before 7 pm.  Very disappointing.  Fortunately I found The Alibi, a delightful British Pub, next door.  The vegetarian pastries were delectable (and the dipping sauce delicious)!  Highly recommend the Alibi!
Highly recommended place.  I had the salmon box for lunch; it was delicious and a big portion at a reasonable   price.

I almost missed this tiny little space next to the much busier bars next door. 3 "bar" seats and four or five other tables. The whole place probably doesn't seat more than 30 - 40 people. Besides me there were only 2 other people dining on a Friday evening (which suited me fine as a solo diner). The service (owners?) were very friendly. Food was good and quick to come out. I had bulgogi buns and sushi roll combo. Bulgogi was awesome!!

Good food. Friendly staff. Food came out very fast. Upper mid-grade fish. Only reason I'm giving this place 4 instead of 5 stars is the price. The price is quite high for the portion size & quality. Overall good restaurant. I will probably be back.

Not open at posted times. We were looking  forward to eating here our last day in DC but were disappointed to find out it was closed. This was on a Saturday at 12:30 and their hours are posted as being open at 11:30. Tried calling and their voicemail wasn't even set up. Too bad.
Delicious. It feels like a little secret place.
Good food, bit pricey. They serve alcohol.
It was pricey, the service and the food was okay.
Good value
The food was good, a bit pricey. The service felt a bit pushy, and not very welcoming.
Total hidden gem.  Small place with super nice staff and absolutely excellent food.  So glad we found this place.

Quick service, but bland and expensive. $14 for a lunch special bento box before the drink. The signature roll: Momoyama has sweet wasabi sauce, like honey mustard, that confused me on salmon (also $14 per roll, healthier than tempura in the boxes, but expensive).
Quiet, clean and pleasant place. The food was tasty and the service​ was good too.
Amazing rolls, great family run business with the best rolls around! Lunch bento boxes are just as great!
Great Japanese option in an otherwise sparse area for family friendly, lighter food.

We arrived near closing time on President's Day 2017. Despite this, we were offered our choice from the bento (box lunch) menu. Promptly served, our lunches were fresh & delicious. Minus 1 star for omitting the tempura dipping sauce.

Passed this place overy the summer so when it came up as a 9 minute walk from the court hour, once we were given a 90 minute lunch break before jury selection, I headed over for sushi. It's really small; there are tables with seating for 12, 3 or 4 seats at the sushi bar, and then maybe 5 seats at the window bar. They have outdoor seating when the weather is nice and you enter in front of a staircase so maybe there is additional seating upstairs. I loved my food and the prices are fairly comparable for Capitol Hill.  The service was friendly and I received my sushi fairly quickly. No complaints really and I'd come back here again. I doubt I'd find any parking, but it's a nice hidden gem on a small backstreet...probably most known to people who work in this area.
The food is GREAT!!! The veggie box was phenominal!!! I will definitely come back again, especially with their low prices!
Super friendly and eager staff, great food, overall excellent experience
This place is fantastic. Definitely worth going to any time you're in DC or live there. I have been there now on two separate trips and it has been worth it both times. It's expensive, but worth it.
Place not open....posted for 11 and we got here at 1130. Not a single person around and doors are locked.

Do not come here. I repeat, do not come here! I have no idea how this place has 4 stars, but it's terrible. The sushi was rubbery and tasted old. They also have no drink selection whatsoever. I tried to order a red wine and all they had was an open bottle of merlot that was in the chiller (so it's probably been there for months). I almost couldn't eat the fish because I thought it would get me sick. $60 later, I hope I don't get sick tonight. Save yourselves!
(Translated by Google) Tasty again 👍  (Original) Lecker gerne wieder 👍
Posted hours say it's open but nobody was there. No sign either. This was on a Saturday night. Didn't get to try the food so I left 2 stars to be fair.
Flies in soy sauce

We selected Momoyama based up Trip Advisor reviews, and the location. We wanted something within walking distance of the sights we were seeing, and this fit the bill. This was one of the top 3 best sushi meals I had EVER had! My wife ordered the sushi & sashimi combo, and loved every piece (their California rolls were tremendous; the had perfectly ripe avocado!) I ordered the Eel Lover's combo, which was also fantastic. I also ordered some tuna and salmon sashimi, and the salmon was some of the best I've ever had. Even their miso soup was memorable; being the first thing we tasted we were both impressed right from the start! It is a very small location - when we arrived we had to sit at their bar (which only seats 3!) We liked it so much that we went back a second time (and the food/service was just as good - this will be a "must eat it" for every future trip to DC for us!!)
Small, cozy restaurant hidden in 2nd St. Good quality sushi, reasonably priced and with a nice homemade touch. Excellent service.
Great sushi, fresh fish, and reasonable prices for the location. Low key atmosphere.

The quantity of food was significantly less than normal. The specialty rolls were half the size of what we expected. We spent $60 total (with tip) for 1 "hot" sake, and 14 small pieces of shtuff. Ultimately, we felt that the quality and quantity was not worth the value. Also, we were the only people there on a Thursday at 7pm. Not a good sign.
great quality sushi in a hole in the wall next to the national mall.
Awesome service along with delicious food. Would definitely recommend to sushi lovers in the area
Loved this place! Best bento box I've ever had! Prices were very reasonable and the food was so good.

We came in late on a rainy Wednesday night. The proprietors were obviously ready to close and go home, but stayed open to serve us. We were their only customers, but they made us feel welcome. We had a sashimi appetizer, some edamame and a couple of Saporos. We were so happy. Then came the hand rolls and sushi rolls. They were perfect, beautiful and very tasty. Thank you Momoyama for making a potentially sad food evening a happy one.
Economic and delicious.
Waiter was quite rude and the pork cutlets were dry like hell. I wouldn't recommend going there
